label: has study descriptor tag
description: 'has study descriptor tag' has study descriptor tag is a relation between a scenario bundle and an oeo class which is used as a study descriptor. The classes in the domain are annotated with oekg in the OEO and are manually chosen. Objects have to be one of the entries in range.

range.label: study report due to legal obligation

label: has part
description: 'has part' a core relation that holds between a whole and its part. A bundle can have four different parts but is not required any. Objects are an URI of the type specified in the range.

label: based on sector division
description: 'based on sector division' based on sector division is a relation between a scenario bundle and a sector division it is based on. Any subclass of sector division plus their individuals are allowed but currently only individuals are used. Objects have to be one of the entries in range.

label: covers sector (shortcut)
description:
'covers sector (shortcut)' A relation between a scenario bundle and a sector that is covered by the study the scenario bundle is about. It is a shortcut relation, see elucidation and associated sparql axiom.

This is a shortcut relation to relate 'scenatio bundle' to 'sector'. The original
relation 'covers sector' relates 'study' (process) to 'sector'.
The shortcut relation should be used to represents these statements:
('scenario bundle 'is about' some 'scenario study'`) and ('scenario study' 'covers
sector' some 'sector') Any subclass of sector plus their individuals are allowed but currently only individuals are used. Objects have to be one of the entries in range.

label: covers technology (shortcut)
description:
'covers technology (shortcut)' A relation between a scenario bundle and a technology that is covered by the study the scenario bundle is about. It is a shortcut relation, see elucidation and associated sparql axiom.

This is a shortcut relation to relate 'scenatio bundle' to 'technology'. The original
relation 'covers technology' relates 'study' (process) to 'technology'.
The shortcut relation should be used to represents these statements:
('scenario bundle 'is about' some 'scenario study'`) and ('scenario study' 'covers
technology' some 'technology') Any subclass of technology plus their individuals are allowed but currently there are no individuals. Objects have to be one of the entries in range.

label: has contact person
description: 'has contact person' A relation that holds between an information content entity and the person to contact with issues about it. Objects are an URI of the type specified in the range.

label: has organisation
description: 'has organisation' A relation that holds between an information content entity and the organisation in which it was created. Objects are an URI of the type specified in the range.

label: has funding source
description: 'has funding source' A relation that holds between an entity and its source of funding. Objects are an URI of the type specified in the range.

label: dc:acronym
description: 'dc:acronym' An Alternative Label that consists of a shortened or abbreviated form of the rdfs:label and is used to denote the entity.

label: dc:abstract
description: 'dc:abstract' A summary of the resource. Definition taken from Dublincore(2020).

label: covers energy carrier (shortcut)
description:
'covers energy carrier (shortcut)' A relation between a scenario bundle and an energy carrier that is covered by the study the scenario bundle is about. It is a shortcut relation, see elucidation and associated sparql axiom.

This is a shortcut relation to relate 'scenatio bundle' to 'energy carrier'. The original relation 'covers energy carrier' relates 'study' (process) to 'energy carrier'.
The shortcut relation should be used to represents these statements:
('scenario bundle 'is about' some 'scenario study'`) and ('scenario study' 'covers energy carrier' some 'energy carrier') Any subclass of energy carrier (and their individuals) plus classes inferred to be energy carrier are allowed. As of now there are no individuals. Objects have to be one of the entries in range.

label: has reference
description: 'has reference' has reference is the relation between a continuant and a reference that points to a relevant resource to the continuant. Links to documents or other ontologies are stored here. Objects are an URI of the type specified in the range.

label: has uuid
description: 'has uuid' has uuid is the relation between a factsheet or report and the 128-bit label used to identify it in a computer system. Uuids are used for internal workings with the oekg.

label: has author
description: 'has author' A relation that holds between an information content entity and its author. Objects are an URI of the type specified in the range.

label: has publication date
description: 'has publication date' has publication date is the relation between a report and the year it was published in.

label: has doi
description: 'has doi' has doi is the relation between a digital object and the literal representing its doi (digital object identifier).

label: has scenario type
description: 'has scenario type' has scenario type is a relation between a scenario factsheet and a subclass of scenario. Subclasses or individuals of scenarios are allowed. As of now, no individuals exist. Objects have to be one of the entries in range.

label: has interacting region
description: 'has interacting region' An is-about-relation between a scenario and an interacting region to indicate an interacting region of a scenario. Objects are an URI of the type specified in the range.

label: has study region
description: 'has study region' An is-about-relation between a scenario and a study region to indicate the study region of a scenario. Objects are an URI of the type specified in the range.

label: has scenario year value
description: 'has scenario year value' has publication date is the relation between a report and the year it was published in. Has scenario year value is a relation between a scenario factsheet and a xsd:dateTime value.

label: has information input (shortcut)
description:
'has information input (shortcut)' A relation between a scenario factsheet and a dataset, where the dataset is an input to the scenario projection process the scenario factsheet is about. It is a shortcut relation, see elucidation and associated sparql axiom.

This is a shortcut relation to relate 'scenatio factsheet' to 'data set'. The original
relation 'has information input' relates 'scenario projection' (process) to 'data set'.
The shortcut relation should be used to represents these statements:
('scenario factsheet' 'is about' some scenario) and
('scenario projection' 'is based on' some scenario) and
('scenario projection' 'has information input' some dataset) Objects are an URI of the type specified in the range.

label: has information output (shortcut)
description:
'has information output (shortcut)' A relation between a scenario factsheet and a dataset, where the dataset is an output of the scenario projection process the scenario factsheet is about. It is a shortcut relation, see elucidation and associated sparql axiom.

This is a shortcut relation to relate 'scenatio factsheet' to 'data set'. The original
relation 'has information output' relates 'scenario projection' (process) to 'data
set'.
The shortcut relation should be used to represents these statements:
('scenario factsheet' 'is about' some scenario) and ('scenario projection' 'is based on' some scenario) and Objects are an URI of the type specified in the range.

label: has iri
description: 'has iri' has iri is a relation between a data item or document and the IRI that identifies it as rescource on the internet. Uuids are used for internal workings with the oekg.

label: oekg:has_id
description: 'oekg:has_id'  Uuids are used for internal workings with the oekg.
